## M22: calling an extern function outside a `raw` block is rejected.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 35 (M21 design): "all extern calls require
## a raw context even if the extern declaration is not
## syntactically marked." Extern declarations are the FFI
## boundary and bypass Rig's ownership / effect contracts.
## Calling an extern from a safe context would silently treat
## a C/Zig API as ownership-safe; the `raw` wrapping
## requirement forces the caller to acknowledge the bargain.

extern puts: fun(String) Int

sub main()
  puts("hi")       # error: extern call requires `raw` block
